# LOG-04 — Graylog Application Logs Collection

> **Task:** Collect Graylog application logs  
> **Author:** Mohamed Amine Namouchi  
> **Date:** June 5, 2026  
> **Status:** ✅ Complete

---

## Context

Graylog application logs contain critical information about the
health of the log pipeline itself:

```
→ Index optimization events
→ System job execution
→ Stream processing errors
→ Input failures (if MikroTik stops sending)
→ Pipeline errors
→ Authentication to Graylog web UI
```

Without collecting these logs, a Graylog failure would be invisible
to Wazuh — the pipeline could stop silently.

---

## Log File

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| **Path** | `/var/log/graylog-server/server.log` |
| **Format** | Custom Graylog format (timestamp + level + component + message) |
| **Agent** | graylog (agent 001) |
| **Retention** | 6 months |

---

## Sample Log Entry

```
2026-06-04T14:37:23.774+02:00 INFO  [OptimizeIndexJob] Optimizing index <graylog_1>.
2026-06-04T14:37:26.595+02:00 INFO  [MongoIndexRangeService] Calculated range of [graylog_1] in [2821ms].
2026-06-04T14:37:26.599+02:00 INFO  [CreateNewSingleIndexRangeJob] Created ranges for index graylog_1.
```

---

## Configuration

Added to `/var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf` on the Graylog server:

```xml
<!-- Graylog application logs — Phase 3 LOG-04 -->
<localfile>
  <log_format>syslog</log_format>
  <location>/var/log/graylog-server/server.log</location>
</localfile>
```

